  "text": "The third measure, the semantic coupling, is represented by the Conceptual Coupling Between Classes (CCBC) metric [CITATION_1] . The CCBC is based on the lexical information derived from comments and identifiers. Two classes are semantically related if the terms present in their comments and identifiers are similar. The conjecture is that if two classes contain similar terms, it is likely that developers used them to describe similar responsibilities. The CCBC between two classes c i and c j is computed as the average textual similarity between all unordered pairs of methods from class c i and class c j . The textual similarity is computed using Latent Semantic Indexing (LSI) [CITATION_2] . The CCBC values are in [0 . . . 1], where 0 represents two classes having a totally different lexicon, while 1 represents two classes containing exactly the same text.",
